1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:14,125 --> 00:00:16,825
(Seo Ji Hye)

3
00:00:21,765 --> 00:00:24,295
(Go Soo)

4
00:00:30,435 --> 00:00:33,475
(Kim Jae Kyung)

5
00:00:38,115 --> 00:00:40,845
(Yoon Je Moon)

6
00:00:47,225 --> 00:00:51,095
(Reverse)

7
00:00:54,825 --> 00:00:55,825
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

8
00:00:55,826 --> 00:00:56,964
(Characters, places, and events are not real.)

9
00:00:56,965 --> 00:00:59,485
(Children and animals were filmed under production guidelines.)

10
00:01:01,805 --> 00:01:05,135
I know what you're thinking. In your imagination,

11
00:01:06,205 --> 00:01:08,245
you've already killed me...

12
00:01:09,175 --> 00:01:10,275
countless times.

13
00:01:10,775 --> 00:01:11,775
Imagination?

14
00:01:13,415 --> 00:01:15,785
You dying at my hands... That's going to be reality.

15
00:01:16,185 --> 00:01:17,265
It's just a matter of time.

16
00:01:18,785 --> 00:01:19,785
Right.

17
00:01:21,525 --> 00:01:23,125
You're just running away.

18
00:01:24,455 --> 00:01:26,795
Hiding in there, hoping everyone will forget you.

19
00:01:27,625 --> 00:01:28,825
Like a pathetic coward.

20
00:01:29,865 --> 00:01:31,465
Shaking in your boots.

21
00:01:33,135 --> 00:01:34,135
Sure.

22
00:01:34,835 --> 00:01:36,805
I guess you could see it that way.

23
00:01:39,675 --> 00:01:41,245
I guess I'm not smart enough...

24
00:01:41,745 --> 00:01:43,715
because that never occurred to me.

25
00:01:44,475 --> 00:01:45,645
Cut the nonsense.

26
00:01:46,715 --> 00:01:48,985
As long as I'm alive, don't even dream of it.

27
00:01:49,045 --> 00:01:50,255
But the thing is,

28
00:01:51,755 --> 00:01:53,155
that's not how the world works.

29
00:01:54,525 --> 00:01:56,955
You can't be so sure about things.

30
00:01:57,355 --> 00:02:00,395
Because you might be the one who changes.

31
00:02:01,495 --> 00:02:02,965
So don't be so reckless...

32
00:02:06,465 --> 00:02:08,765
Are you saying a girl like me can't do anything?

33
00:02:09,205 --> 00:02:13,605
That you can just stall until I run my mouth, get tired and give up.

34
00:02:14,805 --> 00:02:15,805
Is that your plan?

35
00:02:21,415 --> 00:02:22,415
Are you insane?

36
00:02:23,185 --> 00:02:24,455
Is it starting to sink in now?

37
00:02:26,255 --> 00:02:27,355
From just this?

38
00:02:29,285 --> 00:02:30,295
I promise you.

39
00:02:32,095 --> 00:02:33,995
You are going to die at my hands.

40
00:02:35,965 --> 00:02:37,865
No matter what, I guarantee it.

41
00:02:42,435 --> 00:02:45,705
(The Chase)

42
00:02:49,745 --> 00:02:52,515
(CEO Ryu Jun Ho)

43
00:03:02,485 --> 00:03:04,825
This is the guest list for next month's groundbreaking.

44
00:03:05,625 --> 00:03:08,325
We've selected our allies and are ready to send the invites,

45
00:03:09,225 --> 00:03:11,335
but what should we do about the Vice Chairman?

46
00:03:14,605 --> 00:03:17,205
It seems he called the head of Legal yesterday and gave an order.

47
00:03:17,605 --> 00:03:19,805
He's still trying to dig up dirt on you, sir.

48
00:03:20,405 --> 00:03:22,904
I also heard he ordered a major expansion of the Legal Team.

49
00:03:22,905 --> 00:03:24,275
Well, he's a busy man, isn't he?

50
00:03:26,045 --> 00:03:28,115
So, what should I do about his invitation?

51
00:03:29,445 --> 00:03:32,885
Follow procedure. He's Vice Chairman of the parent company, after all.

52
00:03:33,585 --> 00:03:34,585
Understood.

53
00:03:35,485 --> 00:03:36,525
And one more thing...

54
00:03:37,225 --> 00:03:39,555
Could you find out where the Vice Chairman is right now?

55
00:04:15,295 --> 00:04:17,865
We were bound to meet when the time was right anyway.

56
00:04:19,195 --> 00:04:21,081
What is the meaning of this disrespectful stunt?

57
00:04:21,105 --> 00:04:22,105
My apologies.

58
00:04:23,165 --> 00:04:26,905
I asked the person you were with to give us a moment.

59
00:04:27,205 --> 00:04:29,905
It's just that I feel there's a bit of...

60
00:04:30,745 --> 00:04:33,075
a communication problem between us.

61
00:04:34,285 --> 00:04:37,885
What is there for us to communicate about?

62
00:04:38,385 --> 00:04:40,355
When Architecture was founded,

63
00:04:41,885 --> 00:04:44,655
the agreement was that if it met the three-year revenue goal,

64
00:04:44,855 --> 00:04:48,625
the parent firm would give shares to Architecture.

65
00:04:49,295 --> 00:04:51,865
And the terms of the transfer would be mutually negotiated.

66
00:04:52,165 --> 00:04:54,665
This is clearly stated in its articles of incorporation.

67
00:04:57,075 --> 00:04:58,135
As of this past March,

68
00:04:58,975 --> 00:05:03,305
we hit our target revenue. Now, honour the agreement.

69
00:05:03,545 --> 00:05:05,845
The Chairman has just passed away,

70
00:05:07,015 --> 00:05:08,721
and you have the nerve to bring that up now?

71
00:05:08,745 --> 00:05:11,155
- Vice Chairman... - It may be nothing to you,

72
00:05:12,815 --> 00:05:14,955
but our company is in a state of emergency.

73
00:05:16,555 --> 00:05:20,165
Our founder was found as a pile of ashes overnight.

74
00:05:20,625 --> 00:05:22,225
He was burned to a crisp...

75
00:05:22,895 --> 00:05:25,335
to the point where he was unrecognizable.

76
00:05:25,835 --> 00:05:26,835
And yet,

77
00:05:28,035 --> 00:05:29,105
the police are still...

78
00:05:30,375 --> 00:05:33,035
investigating the cause of the Chairman's death.

79
00:05:34,445 --> 00:05:35,545
So just in case...

80
00:05:36,645 --> 00:05:38,445
that this was no simple accident,

81
00:05:39,075 --> 00:05:40,585
I have to be prepared.

82
00:05:41,245 --> 00:05:43,045
Common sense doesn't apply these days.

83
00:05:45,385 --> 00:05:47,484
- Case in point. - Vice Chairman.

84
00:05:47,485 --> 00:05:51,155
Don't take it personally, all right?

85
00:05:51,555 --> 00:05:52,695
This isn't just me talking.

86
00:05:54,195 --> 00:05:55,995
It's the company's official position.

87
00:05:56,595 --> 00:05:59,565
I'm aware you've been snooping around...

88
00:06:02,005 --> 00:06:04,775
and digging into my past.

89
00:06:05,975 --> 00:06:07,805
It's a pointless exercise for both of us.

90
00:06:09,175 --> 00:06:10,275
You should stop.

91
00:06:12,545 --> 00:06:13,885
Are you giving me an order?

92
00:06:20,385 --> 00:06:21,885
You may be the Vice Chairman...

93
00:06:23,525 --> 00:06:25,295
and my senior in this industry,

94
00:06:27,395 --> 00:06:29,765
but my patience has run out.

95
00:06:33,605 --> 00:06:34,605
From now on,

96
00:06:35,335 --> 00:06:37,475
I can't be held responsible for my actions.

97
00:06:38,135 --> 00:06:39,375
So, Vice Chairman...

98
00:06:40,035 --> 00:06:43,245
I suggest you watch your step.

99
00:06:43,745 --> 00:06:44,745
Why, you little...

100
00:06:48,315 --> 00:06:51,985
Then, I'm glad we've come to an understanding.

101
00:06:52,715 --> 00:06:53,955
I'll see myself out.

102
00:07:40,535 --> 00:07:42,635
Have you ever felt real anxiety?

103
00:07:53,045 --> 00:07:55,585
Like everything could fall apart in an instant...

104
00:07:58,685 --> 00:08:02,355
and that someone could just destroy your life?

105
00:08:07,695 --> 00:08:08,725
Sometimes,

106
00:08:10,365 --> 00:08:12,835
I just want to let it all go.

107
00:08:16,505 --> 00:08:18,035
I'm so exhausted.

108
00:08:23,075 --> 00:08:24,275
It's all too much.

109
00:08:31,985 --> 00:08:33,685
I shouldn't have gone.

110
00:08:35,585 --> 00:08:36,625
That day...

111
00:08:40,595 --> 00:08:42,595
I went somewhere I never should have.

112
00:08:43,465 --> 00:08:44,535
See that over there?

113
00:08:46,295 --> 00:08:47,505
That's where we went.

114
00:08:53,875 --> 00:08:56,145
What? He's here.

115
00:08:56,875 --> 00:08:57,975
Myo Jin, let's go.

116
00:09:03,315 --> 00:09:05,685
Jun Ho!

117
00:09:09,985 --> 00:09:12,195
I missed you.

118
00:09:24,775 --> 00:09:26,075
So, what do you think?

119
00:09:28,505 --> 00:09:29,505
Well?

120
00:09:34,645 --> 00:09:35,945
What's with all this furniture?

121
00:09:37,355 --> 00:09:40,625
Didn't you order the pieces I specified?

122
00:09:40,885 --> 00:09:43,555
What do you mean? It's practically the same.

123
00:09:44,255 --> 00:09:45,255
It's just more expensive.

124
00:09:46,855 --> 00:09:47,865
What on earth?

125
00:09:50,165 --> 00:09:52,595
What happened to all of my specifications?

126
00:09:53,065 --> 00:09:55,205
I told you, I picked out something better.

127
00:09:55,905 --> 00:09:58,435
- You don't like it? - I don't dislike it, it's wrong.

128
00:10:00,375 --> 00:10:04,075
I went over every single detail with the builder and wrote it down,

129
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:07,215
- and you just threw it all out. - Are you getting mad at me now?

130
00:10:11,985 --> 00:10:13,485
If you hate it so much,

131
00:10:18,295 --> 00:10:19,415
then just throw it all away.

132
00:10:21,925 --> 00:10:23,995
Tear it all out and fill it with what you want.

133
00:10:25,435 --> 00:10:26,771
There. That should make you happy.

134
00:10:26,795 --> 00:10:28,715
Architecture isn't just the shell of a building.

135
00:10:28,935 --> 00:10:30,655
The inside is part of the architecture too.

136
00:10:31,035 --> 00:10:32,835
This may be our villa,

137
00:10:32,875 --> 00:10:36,145
but it's still, undeniably, one of my works in Korea.

138
00:10:36,475 --> 00:10:37,615
You're right.

139
00:10:38,015 --> 00:10:40,685
This is a space just for the two of us.

140
00:10:42,015 --> 00:10:43,745
And I happen to love it just the way it is.

141
00:10:44,315 --> 00:10:47,055
If I love it, shouldn't that be enough for you?

142
00:10:54,525 --> 00:10:56,765
Can't you just drop...

143
00:10:58,065 --> 00:10:59,545
the whole perfectionist act for once?

144
00:11:00,565 --> 00:11:01,605
Please?

145
00:11:04,075 --> 00:11:05,275
You're such a control freak.

146
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:13,445
Say hi. This is my friend, Myo Jin.

147
00:11:25,725 --> 00:11:26,805
You know who she is, right?

148
00:11:35,405 --> 00:11:37,635
You have a villa like this in every country?

149
00:11:37,835 --> 00:11:39,795
The others are just properties we build and sell,

150
00:11:40,845 --> 00:11:42,005
but not this one.

151
00:11:45,875 --> 00:11:47,245
A certain someone designed it,

152
00:11:47,815 --> 00:11:49,015
so I insisted on having it.

153
00:11:49,485 --> 00:11:50,485
The design?

154
00:11:52,185 --> 00:11:54,265
You mean the one that was half-done by someone else?

155
00:11:54,685 --> 00:11:55,725
Not this again.

156
00:11:57,195 --> 00:11:58,195
Cheers!

157
00:12:03,565 --> 00:12:06,665
Your father is really incredible.

158
00:12:07,265 --> 00:12:10,505
I can't even begin to imagine the scale of his business.

159
00:12:12,205 --> 00:12:14,975
Myo Jin, you seem so fascinated by my dad.

160
00:12:15,845 --> 00:12:17,445
She's always asking me about my dad.

161
00:12:22,045 --> 00:12:24,385
You two...

162
00:12:26,585 --> 00:12:27,685
are so much alike.

163
00:12:28,755 --> 00:12:31,025
- How so? - You both admire my dad.

164
00:12:32,055 --> 00:12:35,125
You're always saying it, Jun Ho. How you want to succeed like him.

165
00:12:37,635 --> 00:12:41,205
And Myo Jin is always saying how much she wants to meet him.

166
00:12:43,465 --> 00:12:46,075
- You do? - I did?

167
00:12:46,505 --> 00:12:49,875
He said he's coming back to Korea soon anyway,

168
00:12:50,375 --> 00:12:51,615
so you can both meet him then.

169
00:12:52,115 --> 00:12:53,515
The three of us can all go see him.

170
00:12:54,115 --> 00:12:55,675
So he's really planning on coming back?

171
00:12:56,185 --> 00:12:58,785
Who knows if he's just talking or if he's serious.

172
00:13:00,925 --> 00:13:01,955
Cheers.

173
00:13:27,515 --> 00:13:29,145
I'm going to run to the restroom.

174
00:13:50,305 --> 00:13:51,335
Myo Jin.

175
00:13:52,375 --> 00:13:53,435
I'm so sorry.

176
00:13:54,805 --> 00:13:55,945
I thought you were Hee Soo.

177
00:13:56,245 --> 00:13:58,815
Oh, no, it's okay. It's my fault.

178
00:13:59,315 --> 00:14:01,075
I shouldn't have borrowed Hee Soo's clothes.

179
00:14:02,015 --> 00:14:03,745
I didn't realise I'd be staying this long.

180
00:14:04,715 --> 00:14:05,715
I'm sorry.

181
00:14:06,315 --> 00:14:08,125
Gosh, I'm not even drunk,

182
00:14:08,825 --> 00:14:10,705
but I can't believe I made a mistake like that.

183
00:14:11,095 --> 00:14:12,155
I am so sorry.

184
00:14:15,025 --> 00:14:16,395
Jun Ho!

185
00:14:17,495 --> 00:14:19,735
Did we finish all the champagne?

186
00:14:20,865 --> 00:14:21,935
Is it all gone?

187
00:14:29,645 --> 00:14:32,175
Hey, that looks great on you.

188
00:14:32,875 --> 00:14:34,515
You should've changed into it sooner.

189
00:14:35,245 --> 00:14:36,245
I guess so.

190
00:14:36,445 --> 00:14:38,591
What are you doing all by yourself? You must be bored.

191
00:14:38,615 --> 00:14:39,975
Come on, let's have another drink.

192
00:14:40,585 --> 00:14:41,725
I'm good for now.

193
00:14:42,125 --> 00:14:44,225
- I'm going to get some fresh air. - Why?

194
00:14:44,695 --> 00:14:45,725
Feeling cooped up?

195
00:14:46,555 --> 00:14:48,555
Then how about we take the yacht out on the water?

196
00:14:48,825 --> 00:14:50,995
No, that's okay. You two enjoy your time together.

197
00:15:13,955 --> 00:15:15,655
Stop.

198
00:15:17,595 --> 00:15:18,595
Why?

199
00:15:19,695 --> 00:15:20,995
I said stop.

200
00:15:23,665 --> 00:15:25,225
What's gotten into you all of a sudden?

201
00:15:28,805 --> 00:15:30,065
Something's off.

202
00:15:32,305 --> 00:15:33,575
Everything feels different.

203
00:15:50,725 --> 00:15:51,925
Are you still on your meds?

204
00:15:53,455 --> 00:15:54,465
Why?

205
00:15:55,095 --> 00:15:56,095
Are you worried?

206
00:15:59,035 --> 00:16:02,165
- What are you doing? Give it to me. - Let go! Are you crazy?

207
00:16:02,235 --> 00:16:04,535
I told you not to up your dosage on your own!

208
00:16:12,275 --> 00:16:13,275
You...

209
00:16:14,785 --> 00:16:16,215
You've really lost it.

210
00:16:19,055 --> 00:16:20,585
What my dad told you...

211
00:16:22,025 --> 00:16:23,355
You haven't forgotten, have you?

212
00:16:24,395 --> 00:16:25,895
All those gifts he gives you...

213
00:16:27,865 --> 00:16:29,725
They don't come for free.

214
00:16:32,095 --> 00:16:33,095
You know that, right?

215
00:17:18,175 --> 00:17:19,175
Get in.

216
00:17:19,515 --> 00:17:21,815
- Sorry? - I said get in. Now.

217
00:17:59,385 --> 00:18:01,185
Is something going on with Hee Soo?

218
00:18:02,355 --> 00:18:05,155
How long have you and Hee Soo been close?

219
00:18:08,565 --> 00:18:09,765
Then you must know.

220
00:18:11,165 --> 00:18:13,135
That she's not an easy person to be close to.

221
00:18:20,075 --> 00:18:21,075
It's just...

222
00:18:22,205 --> 00:18:23,405
we're friends.

223
00:18:23,975 --> 00:18:24,975
It seems like...

224
00:18:25,745 --> 00:18:28,515
Hee Soo is extremely fond of you.

225
00:18:29,115 --> 00:18:30,245
But what about you?

226
00:18:31,815 --> 00:18:33,315
What do you like about her?

227
00:18:36,025 --> 00:18:37,625
You have to understand, Jun Ho.

228
00:18:39,255 --> 00:18:42,195
When women haven't met in a while, they can get a little cranky.

229
00:18:43,665 --> 00:18:45,295
Hee Soo is just...

230
00:18:46,465 --> 00:18:48,065
sensitive than most women, that's all.

231
00:18:58,945 --> 00:19:00,045
You seem to know a lot...

232
00:19:00,915 --> 00:19:02,145
about Hee Soo.

233
00:19:04,015 --> 00:19:05,455
You should go back now.

234
00:19:07,185 --> 00:19:09,355
I'm going to stay out a little longer.

235
00:19:09,785 --> 00:19:10,995
Aren't you curious?

236
00:19:13,655 --> 00:19:16,795
- About what? - If earlier was really an accident.

237
00:19:19,665 --> 00:19:21,365
You must know as well.

238
00:19:24,065 --> 00:19:25,535
That it was no accident.

239
00:19:26,975 --> 00:19:28,305
I'm going back.

240
00:19:29,275 --> 00:19:30,995
I don't want to give anyone the wrong idea.

241
00:19:31,415 --> 00:19:33,345
What wrong idea?

242
00:20:24,295 --> 00:20:25,295
(Recording)

243
00:20:28,665 --> 00:20:31,535
I stole Jun Ho from Hee Soo.

244
00:20:33,275 --> 00:20:34,675
I must have been out of my mind.

245
00:20:36,005 --> 00:20:38,245
I betrayed our friendship...

246
00:20:39,015 --> 00:20:42,215
and just hid it, pretending I didn't know a thing.

247
00:20:50,125 --> 00:20:51,295
But did Hee Soo...

248
00:20:52,095 --> 00:20:53,095
really...

249
00:20:56,195 --> 00:20:57,765
not know anything?

250
00:21:28,995 --> 00:21:30,495
Were you out by the beach?

251
00:21:38,605 --> 00:21:39,605
Yes.

252
00:21:50,815 --> 00:21:52,255
What took you so long?

253
00:21:56,055 --> 00:21:58,155
I guess I was there a little long.

254
00:21:59,495 --> 00:22:00,755
Sounds like you had fun.

255
00:22:06,695 --> 00:22:08,805
- What about Jun Ho? - What?

256
00:22:09,035 --> 00:22:11,235
Jun Ho. I'm asking if you saw him.

257
00:22:12,605 --> 00:22:14,435
I thought I saw him heading toward the beach.

258
00:22:16,445 --> 00:22:17,945
I wouldn't know.

259
00:22:24,785 --> 00:22:26,055
Funny, isn't it?

260
00:22:28,225 --> 00:22:30,455
What? What is?

261
00:22:31,025 --> 00:22:32,695
Everyone's under the same delusion.

262
00:22:35,195 --> 00:22:37,295
They think they can outrun the tide.

263
00:22:38,865 --> 00:22:40,165
But the ocean...

264
00:22:42,005 --> 00:22:43,635
rushes in much faster than you think.

265
00:22:45,405 --> 00:22:47,435
By the time you realise it, it's already too late.

266
00:22:48,875 --> 00:22:49,945
Before you know it,

267
00:22:51,175 --> 00:22:53,045
you're in way over your head.

268
00:23:00,485 --> 00:23:02,955
So you'd better be careful.

269
00:23:13,595 --> 00:23:14,765
You must be tired.

270
00:23:37,955 --> 00:23:39,275
This is yours, isn't it, Myo Jin?

271
00:23:43,395 --> 00:23:44,395
Give it to me.

272
00:23:44,735 --> 00:23:45,965
Hee Soo was right.

273
00:23:47,335 --> 00:23:50,065
- About what? - That you're a great artist.

274
00:23:50,835 --> 00:23:52,635
She told me I should invest in your work now.

275
00:23:53,505 --> 00:23:54,875
Hee Soo was just kidding.

276
00:23:57,075 --> 00:23:59,145
Didn't you know? Hee Soo doesn't joke about that.

277
00:24:01,885 --> 00:24:04,445
Myo Jin. Do you happen to draw people too?

278
00:24:05,015 --> 00:24:07,285
If you need a portrait, ask Hee Soo.

279
00:24:09,485 --> 00:24:10,965
She's a much better artist than I am.

280
00:24:12,095 --> 00:24:13,695
I'm sure she's a great artist,

281
00:24:14,625 --> 00:24:15,625
but I'm...

282
00:24:17,095 --> 00:24:18,735
interested in your art.

283
00:24:24,005 --> 00:24:25,075
One mistake...

284
00:24:25,635 --> 00:24:27,005
was more than enough.

285
00:24:27,535 --> 00:24:30,345
It was so painful I wanted to die. So please, stop toying with me.

286
00:24:32,345 --> 00:24:33,774
- Myo Jin. - I'm not comfortable...

287
00:24:33,775 --> 00:24:34,785
talking to you like this.

288
00:24:35,745 --> 00:24:37,625
You said you went to Seoul this morning, right?

289
00:24:39,255 --> 00:24:40,555
I'm going tomorrow as well.

290
00:24:41,455 --> 00:24:42,655
In fact, my office,

291
00:24:43,655 --> 00:24:46,094
- isn't far from Hee Soo's place. - Please, just stop it.

292
00:24:46,095 --> 00:24:47,295
Mono Architecture.

293
00:24:48,325 --> 00:24:50,645
You can find it on your GPS. Feel free to stop by anytime.

294
00:25:03,145 --> 00:25:04,205
Scum...

295
00:25:06,975 --> 00:25:09,985
To Hee Soo, I was scum. A monster.

296
00:25:12,885 --> 00:25:16,155
I ruined everything, and I stabbed Hee Soo in the back.

297
00:25:23,825 --> 00:25:26,835
Imagine being born in a sandpit in the desert.

298
00:25:28,705 --> 00:25:29,865
Do you know what that's like?

299
00:25:31,405 --> 00:25:33,105
You wash yourself with sand...

300
00:25:35,105 --> 00:25:37,645
and eat sand as if it were food,

301
00:25:40,315 --> 00:25:42,885
just slowly grinding away until you die.

302
00:25:46,315 --> 00:25:48,485
I guess that's what I've become.

303
00:25:54,925 --> 00:25:57,025
Jun Ho betrayed Hee Soo too.

304
00:25:58,895 --> 00:26:01,665
He deceived and destroyed her, just like I did.

305
00:26:04,235 --> 00:26:06,705
We made an irreversible choice,

306
00:26:08,645 --> 00:26:10,875
and Hee Soo died all alone in agony.

307
00:26:14,675 --> 00:26:17,815
Those vile beasts, Ham Myo Jin and Ryu Jun Ho...

308
00:26:18,455 --> 00:26:20,015
We killed Hee Soo.

309
00:26:24,485 --> 00:26:27,155
She must have been so lonely and in so much pain.

310
00:26:36,335 --> 00:26:37,465
Even if it's too late,

311
00:26:40,035 --> 00:26:41,975
I want to pay the price for what we did.

312
00:27:39,765 --> 00:27:40,995
What were you thinking?

313
00:27:45,835 --> 00:27:47,435
It's not a matter of good or bad.

314
00:27:47,505 --> 00:27:51,545
This is nothing more than a personal vanity project.

315
00:27:52,745 --> 00:27:56,515
It's not a traditional "object" form in any way.

316
00:28:01,385 --> 00:28:02,385
Thank you.

317
00:28:03,885 --> 00:28:08,095
You've understood my intention perfectly, sir.

318
00:28:08,365 --> 00:28:13,195
This is for the largest museum in all of Asia right here in Korea.

319
00:28:13,665 --> 00:28:17,065
Not only in scale, but in artistry, technical prowess, and creativity,

320
00:28:17,135 --> 00:28:21,435
it will serve as the benchmark for all of Korean architecture.

321
00:28:21,505 --> 00:28:22,805
With a design like this,

322
00:28:24,105 --> 00:28:26,975
what exactly are you contributing, Mr. Ryu?

323
00:28:27,545 --> 00:28:28,545
Sir.

324
00:28:29,515 --> 00:28:33,415
When most architects begin a new project,

325
00:28:34,115 --> 00:28:37,155
they start by referencing past archetypes.

326
00:28:37,725 --> 00:28:40,555
But as an architect,

327
00:28:41,565 --> 00:28:45,635
- I reject that approach. - Overconfidence is near arrogance.

328
00:28:45,765 --> 00:28:48,305
Constantly referencing past examples...

329
00:28:49,605 --> 00:28:52,275
only leads to an accumulation of derivative work.

330
00:28:53,135 --> 00:28:55,174
Unless we escape this framework,

331
00:28:55,175 --> 00:28:57,245
Korean architecture will ultimately be...

332
00:28:57,305 --> 00:28:59,575
defined by homogenous designs.

333
00:29:01,015 --> 00:29:03,645
You can criticize my work, of course,

334
00:29:05,385 --> 00:29:07,584
but the more that efforts and attempts like mine come together,

335
00:29:07,585 --> 00:29:09,285
I'm confident Korean architecture...

336
00:29:11,025 --> 00:29:13,355
will break free of self-replication.

337
00:29:15,095 --> 00:29:19,895
That's why I chose the concept as Silence for the Sake of Essence.

338
00:29:21,835 --> 00:29:26,635
By eliminating the intrusive functions of conventional buildings,

339
00:29:26,705 --> 00:29:29,875
we can focus on its contents, the people, the music,

340
00:29:30,275 --> 00:29:35,245
and on faithfully capturing the very essence of life itself.

341
00:29:46,895 --> 00:29:48,525
(HGA Distribution)

342
00:29:51,395 --> 00:29:53,165
Spit it out, you jerk!

343
00:29:54,165 --> 00:29:55,835
What did I do that was so wrong?

344
00:29:56,205 --> 00:29:59,805
Is taking a nap after lunch a capital offence?

345
00:29:59,975 --> 00:30:03,545
Besides, you had one of the others do my work for me anyway.

346
00:30:03,975 --> 00:30:07,615
So in the end, it's not like I caused any real trouble,

347
00:30:07,715 --> 00:30:08,745
is what I'm saying.

348
00:30:09,245 --> 00:30:12,615
Gosh, this jerk sure loves to hear himself talk.

349
00:30:13,855 --> 00:30:16,295
Hey, you beat the crap out of the site manager for no reason,

350
00:30:16,525 --> 00:30:18,955
and you say that's not wrong? Then what is?

351
00:30:20,795 --> 00:30:23,925
That jerk of a manager has it in for me.

352
00:30:24,125 --> 00:30:26,965
He's always on my back,

353
00:30:27,295 --> 00:30:29,105
picking a fight over every little thing.

354
00:30:29,705 --> 00:30:31,035
What was I supposed to do?

355
00:30:31,605 --> 00:30:33,405
A person's patience has a limit.

356
00:30:34,975 --> 00:30:39,115
- Doesn't it? - A limit? Are you a credit card?

357
00:30:39,415 --> 00:30:40,415
A limit? For you?

358
00:30:41,245 --> 00:30:43,314
Look at this jerk, dumber than me.

359
00:30:43,315 --> 00:30:45,385
Listen to him think he's hot stuff.

360
00:30:45,655 --> 00:30:48,285
Hey! You got paid, so just do your job.

361
00:30:48,525 --> 00:30:50,961
While everyone else is working, you're just passed out asleep.

362
00:30:50,985 --> 00:30:53,255
You think you can just beat him up, you scum?

363
00:30:53,925 --> 00:30:55,165
You want a piece of me?

364
00:30:55,695 --> 00:30:58,125
Okay? I would just...

365
00:31:00,665 --> 00:31:02,985
Did everything I told you go in one ear and out the other?

366
00:31:04,135 --> 00:31:05,535
What are you talking about?

367
00:31:05,775 --> 00:31:09,705
An idiot with a bad memory. That's why he always makes trouble.

368
00:31:10,975 --> 00:31:12,575
When you act like a bum...

369
00:31:12,875 --> 00:31:16,485
in a foreign country, you make us Joseonjok look bad.

370
00:31:16,685 --> 00:31:18,315
Didn't I tell you that?

371
00:31:22,185 --> 00:31:25,225
The reason we Joseonjok get treated like nonsense wherever we go...

372
00:31:25,295 --> 00:31:29,425
is because of idiots like him making trouble for everyone.

373
00:31:29,895 --> 00:31:32,535
Didn't I tell you that? Does none of this ring a bell?

374
00:31:32,765 --> 00:31:34,065
- I remember. - I remember.

375
00:31:36,165 --> 00:31:38,205
- I remember. - What?

376
00:31:39,705 --> 00:31:41,335
So you remember, and you did it anyway?

377
00:31:45,245 --> 00:31:48,145
So then, because of you,

378
00:31:49,385 --> 00:31:52,055
all of us Joseonjok are going to get a bad name again.

379
00:31:53,955 --> 00:31:57,285
- How will you take responsibility? - Boss, I was wrong.

380
00:31:58,025 --> 00:32:00,895
From now on, I won't eat, and I won't even work out.

381
00:32:00,955 --> 00:32:02,425
I swear I'll do nothing but work.

382
00:32:05,735 --> 00:32:07,235
That idiot.

383
00:32:07,495 --> 00:32:09,905
Make him think about what he's done until I give the word.

384
00:32:09,965 --> 00:32:12,105
Boss! Please, have mercy.

385
00:32:12,205 --> 00:32:15,035
I was wrong! Please, just spare me this once.

386
00:32:15,105 --> 00:32:17,075
Boss!

387
00:32:17,805 --> 00:32:19,375
- Spare me! - Shut it!

388
00:32:19,775 --> 00:32:22,391
The way you're screaming, it sounds like you're going to your execution.

389
00:32:22,415 --> 00:32:24,645
Boss!

390
00:32:25,515 --> 00:32:26,515
Boss!

391
00:32:27,315 --> 00:32:29,755
Something terrible's happened. Hae Sik...

392
00:32:30,455 --> 00:32:32,815
got beaten up by some thugs and was rushed to the hospital.

393
00:32:33,125 --> 00:32:34,625
Wait, who?

394
00:32:35,055 --> 00:32:36,895
Your brother, Boss. Hae Sik.

395
00:32:45,035 --> 00:32:46,175
This is so unfair.

396
00:32:47,505 --> 00:32:49,705
I even got disciplined at work today...

397
00:32:50,575 --> 00:32:52,945
and now this? What did I do to deserve this?

398
00:32:53,515 --> 00:32:55,415
Are you sure that's the whole story?

399
00:32:55,945 --> 00:32:58,955
- You really did nothing wrong? - Boss, you know me better.

400
00:33:00,015 --> 00:33:03,255
Have you ever seen me cause trouble anywhere?

401
00:33:03,525 --> 00:33:04,625
Because of me,

402
00:33:05,525 --> 00:33:07,095
have our people...

403
00:33:07,455 --> 00:33:11,265
lost face even once?

404
00:33:13,035 --> 00:33:14,765
You see the state I'm in,

405
00:33:15,405 --> 00:33:17,735
and you still don't believe your own brother?

406
00:33:20,735 --> 00:33:22,175
Do you remember where it was?

407
00:33:22,275 --> 00:33:24,475
I don't know where the guys who did this to me are,

408
00:33:24,845 --> 00:33:27,085
but I know where to find the guy who drugged our drinks.

409
00:33:28,115 --> 00:33:30,085
My friend gets out of the hospital tomorrow,

410
00:33:30,745 --> 00:33:32,455
so I can ask him then.

411
00:33:33,215 --> 00:33:35,095
Then why didn't you tell me any of this before?

412
00:33:35,225 --> 00:33:37,725
I know you just got back from a long-awaited trip home.

413
00:33:38,025 --> 00:33:40,225
It's not exactly something to brag about, is it?

414
00:33:42,165 --> 00:33:45,495
It's bad enough getting beat up in a foreign country.

415
00:33:46,535 --> 00:33:50,065
If word gets out that I'm some pathetic loser,

416
00:33:50,465 --> 00:33:53,405
- what about my reputation? - Your reputation?

417
00:33:53,735 --> 00:33:56,745
Then out of all those guys, why'd you get beat up the worst?

418
00:33:58,205 --> 00:34:00,375
If I don't look out for our guys, who will?

419
00:34:00,975 --> 00:34:04,745
You think I wanted to get beat up like this?

420
00:34:08,285 --> 00:34:09,325
Gosh, it hurts.

421
00:34:10,385 --> 00:34:11,525
All right.

422
00:34:14,855 --> 00:34:16,595
Look at the state of you.

423
00:34:18,995 --> 00:34:20,965
(Jongdo Construction Union)

424
00:34:21,035 --> 00:34:24,765
Boss, who's that wench shacking up with now?

425
00:34:24,935 --> 00:34:27,275
She's bound to contact you again soon, right?

426
00:34:28,235 --> 00:34:32,045
When she does, just signal me. I'll take care of the rest...

427
00:34:34,675 --> 00:34:37,315
Why do you always say the same thing every time you show up?

428
00:34:37,385 --> 00:34:38,915
You're like a broken record.

429
00:34:39,585 --> 00:34:42,955
If she shows up here,

430
00:34:43,155 --> 00:34:45,185
and I give you a heads-up,

431
00:34:46,695 --> 00:34:50,225
- ...you'll handle it, right? - You just sit back...

432
00:34:50,525 --> 00:34:52,695
and enjoy the spoils, Boss.

433
00:34:53,035 --> 00:34:54,195
What's your angle?

434
00:34:54,735 --> 00:34:55,735
What?

435
00:34:55,805 --> 00:35:00,005
Why drag me into something you can do on your own?

436
00:35:00,405 --> 00:35:03,645
- What are you talking about? - You want me to spell it out?

437
00:35:14,115 --> 00:35:15,725
If that kid ends up dead,

438
00:35:17,755 --> 00:35:20,355
you'd be the one who did it,

439
00:35:20,655 --> 00:35:22,724
but I'd have her blood on my hands.

440
00:35:22,725 --> 00:35:25,195
If you were to act alone,

441
00:35:25,395 --> 00:35:26,495
since I...

442
00:35:27,135 --> 00:35:29,605
would know it was your doing,

443
00:35:31,805 --> 00:35:35,875
you'd be afraid I'd retaliate. And after her,

444
00:35:35,945 --> 00:35:37,605
you'd have to get rid of me next.

445
00:35:38,645 --> 00:35:40,645
So you were probably wondering what to do.

446
00:35:41,375 --> 00:35:43,045
Quite the dilemma for you.

447
00:35:44,315 --> 00:35:46,185
That's why from the very beginning,

448
00:35:48,085 --> 00:35:50,455
you've been trying to drag me into this.

449
00:35:52,295 --> 00:35:54,425
Boss, wait, you've got it all wrong...

450
00:35:54,495 --> 00:35:56,865
You, pull a stunt that transparent?

451
00:35:58,125 --> 00:36:00,685
A guy who crawled his way up from a construction site hustler...

452
00:36:01,595 --> 00:36:04,265
to a chauffeur for a rich family?

453
00:36:09,945 --> 00:36:11,545
Bring me money!

454
00:36:12,645 --> 00:36:16,545
I don't care what your scheme is! I'll do whatever you want!

455
00:36:18,915 --> 00:36:20,285
Have you already forgotten...

456
00:36:20,815 --> 00:36:22,825
what it takes to get me on board?

457
00:36:30,795 --> 00:36:34,335
If you come to me empty-handed and try to pull this crap again,

458
00:36:35,135 --> 00:36:36,735
it won't be her.

459
00:36:37,405 --> 00:36:39,705
You'll be the first to die by my hand.

460
00:36:42,875 --> 00:36:44,805
You got it? Now, get lost.

461
00:36:47,315 --> 00:36:48,515
You're tiring me out.

462
00:37:07,435 --> 00:37:08,705
You're still up?

463
00:37:15,405 --> 00:37:16,405
Are you okay?

464
00:37:17,205 --> 00:37:18,915
I have something to ask you.

465
00:37:19,945 --> 00:37:21,645
And I need you to be honest with me.

466
00:37:24,445 --> 00:37:25,455
Okay.

467
00:37:26,255 --> 00:37:27,255
What is it?

468
00:37:34,795 --> 00:37:36,195
It's about Choi Hee Soo.

469
00:37:37,695 --> 00:37:40,965
Why haven't you told me about your relationship with Hee Soo?

470
00:37:44,305 --> 00:37:46,335
- Myo Jin... - You said you barely knew her...

471
00:37:48,005 --> 00:37:49,005
How could you...

472
00:37:49,905 --> 00:37:51,675
How could you lie to me like that?

473
00:37:55,115 --> 00:37:57,885
It's too much for you to hear while you're still recovering.

474
00:38:01,215 --> 00:38:03,625
That you abandoned Hee Soo, your girlfriend,

475
00:38:04,425 --> 00:38:05,624
and that I betrayed my friend...

476
00:38:05,625 --> 00:38:07,355
That's what's "too much" for me?

477
00:38:08,865 --> 00:38:09,865
No.

478
00:38:10,865 --> 00:38:13,035
That's something I absolutely need to know.

479
00:38:15,465 --> 00:38:17,935
- Myo Jin. - You hid it, scared I'd be shocked,

480
00:38:18,635 --> 00:38:20,775
and that you'd tell me everything once I recovered?

481
00:38:22,075 --> 00:38:24,875
Were you just going to say Hee Soo, abandoned by scum like you and me,

482
00:38:25,875 --> 00:38:28,275
died in an accident, just gone? Is that it?

483
00:38:43,365 --> 00:38:44,365
I'm sorry.

484
00:38:47,065 --> 00:38:48,295
I was selfish.

485
00:38:56,075 --> 00:38:57,945
But I didn't hide it on purpose.

486
00:38:59,175 --> 00:39:00,675
How could I possibly hide it?

487
00:39:03,745 --> 00:39:06,785
You were going to remember everything eventually.

488
00:39:07,855 --> 00:39:09,955
It was hard for me to talk about,

489
00:39:11,355 --> 00:39:14,595
and I knew it would be hard for you to hear,

490
00:39:16,365 --> 00:39:19,765
so I guess I wanted to put it off for as long as I could.

491
00:39:21,295 --> 00:39:22,565
It's all my fault.

492
00:39:25,035 --> 00:39:26,775
Hee Soo was struggling.

493
00:39:29,075 --> 00:39:33,445
She said people were just using her. That she was all alone.

494
00:39:34,845 --> 00:39:38,485
The only people she trusted were you and me.

495
00:39:39,885 --> 00:39:42,115
Hee Soo was already on the edge.

496
00:39:49,095 --> 00:39:52,565
Darn, every time I try something, it all goes sideways.

497
00:40:05,445 --> 00:40:06,745
What happened to Hee Soo?

498
00:40:08,415 --> 00:40:10,985
The investigation is still ongoing. We'll find out in time.

499
00:40:11,645 --> 00:40:14,785
What was I doing there that day?

500
00:40:16,725 --> 00:40:17,885
Like Detective Woo said,

501
00:40:18,555 --> 00:40:20,855
I can't remember why my accident happened...

502
00:40:22,125 --> 00:40:24,125
near the vacation home, no matter how hard I try.

503
00:40:34,835 --> 00:40:38,175
I thought none of Choi Hee Soo's accounts were left.

504
00:40:38,505 --> 00:40:40,375
The forensics team had a tough time with it.

505
00:40:41,045 --> 00:40:43,744
A young US citizen with no social media?

506
00:40:43,745 --> 00:40:45,715
Does that make any sense?

507
00:40:46,385 --> 00:40:48,185
She had them. Someone must have deleted them.

508
00:40:48,385 --> 00:40:50,125
Maybe she deleted them herself.

509
00:40:51,085 --> 00:40:53,995
They were deleted after the incident.

510
00:40:54,555 --> 00:40:55,555
No way.

511
00:41:00,395 --> 00:41:03,105
Wait. Choi Hee Soo and Ham Myo Jin knew each other?

512
00:41:03,605 --> 00:41:04,605
They were friends?

513
00:41:05,305 --> 00:41:07,435
Hey, what do you make of this?

514
00:41:08,375 --> 00:41:10,245
This is an engagement photo.

515
00:41:11,375 --> 00:41:14,115
Choi Hee Soo and Ryu Jun Ho?

516
00:41:15,785 --> 00:41:18,985
Gosh, this Ham Myo Jin woman gives me the creeps.

517
00:41:19,655 --> 00:41:22,254
She pretended to know nothing.

518
00:41:22,255 --> 00:41:23,785
This was the reason.

519
00:41:25,555 --> 00:41:27,395
After Choi Hee Soo died in an accident,

520
00:41:27,825 --> 00:41:30,105
her "friend," Ham Myo Jin, swooped in and took her place?

521
00:41:32,465 --> 00:41:34,665
The way she's sticking to this cliche story,

522
00:41:36,005 --> 00:41:38,405
you almost have to wonder if she really did lose her memory.

523
00:41:41,905 --> 00:41:44,145
I know you're busy, so thank you for making time for me.

524
00:41:44,375 --> 00:41:46,175
I hope you'll find everything to your liking.

525
00:41:46,645 --> 00:41:49,185
I've made reservations at a special place for dinner.

526
00:41:51,415 --> 00:41:54,615
When have your plans ever been anything but special?

527
00:42:02,525 --> 00:42:05,265
It's looking like Oh Sang Il...

528
00:42:05,625 --> 00:42:07,965
is going to be appointed head of the judge committee.

529
00:42:09,235 --> 00:42:12,675
The other members are all unanimously recommending him.

530
00:42:13,205 --> 00:42:16,975
It's not just me. Everyone in our industry is on edge.

531
00:42:17,345 --> 00:42:18,705
On edge? There's no need for that.

532
00:42:19,345 --> 00:42:20,745
After all, with this project,

533
00:42:21,115 --> 00:42:23,645
there are only a handful of companies that can handle it.

534
00:42:25,755 --> 00:42:27,431
I will ensure it's a success, no matter what.

535
00:42:27,455 --> 00:42:30,785
I know very well what you're capable of.

536
00:42:32,695 --> 00:42:33,725
But there is something.

537
00:42:34,995 --> 00:42:37,425
Do you happen to know someone named Ryu Jun Ho?

538
00:42:38,125 --> 00:42:40,965
He's still a bit green, but he's got the fundamentals down.

539
00:42:41,635 --> 00:42:43,395
He hasn't been back in the country for long,

540
00:42:43,805 --> 00:42:45,775
but the projects he's worked on have been decent.

541
00:42:47,205 --> 00:42:48,205
Why do you ask?

542
00:42:48,705 --> 00:42:53,045
I heard he paid a secret visit to Oh Sang Il.

543
00:42:54,375 --> 00:42:56,255
The timing's a bit suspicious, don't you think?

544
00:42:57,085 --> 00:43:00,355
He's not even eligible to apply with no domestic experience.

545
00:43:00,485 --> 00:43:02,445
Those requirements have already been made public.

546
00:43:03,055 --> 00:43:06,995
You know they're announcing committee members next week, right?

547
00:43:07,395 --> 00:43:08,395
Yes, Assemblyman.

548
00:43:09,065 --> 00:43:10,065
At that time,

549
00:43:11,865 --> 00:43:15,195
a revised clause will be announced as well.

550
00:43:15,735 --> 00:43:19,035
Oh Sang Il apparently requested it himself.

551
00:43:19,905 --> 00:43:24,075
He wants a merit-based review, without barriers or discrimination.

552
00:43:24,745 --> 00:43:28,345
Sounds just like something Oh Sang Il would say.

553
00:43:30,015 --> 00:43:33,755
Still, I wouldn't get too complacent if I were you.

554
00:43:34,785 --> 00:43:37,125
There's always a loophole somewhere.

555
00:43:47,295 --> 00:43:48,295
I'm so sorry.

556
00:43:49,865 --> 00:43:51,905
For just showing up like this during your break.

557
00:43:52,365 --> 00:43:53,805
Like your memories, you mean?

558
00:43:59,175 --> 00:44:03,415
Before he met me, Jun Ho was already engaged.

559
00:44:05,215 --> 00:44:07,015
And I was friends with her.

560
00:44:07,685 --> 00:44:09,085
I don't know why I did it,

561
00:44:11,025 --> 00:44:13,795
but I found out that I'm the one who stole him from her.

562
00:44:19,025 --> 00:44:22,765
I went through all that, seeking a profound truth.

563
00:44:25,335 --> 00:44:26,805
And all I found out...

564
00:44:29,445 --> 00:44:30,685
is what a horrible person I am.

565
00:44:34,745 --> 00:44:35,745
Doctor...

566
00:44:36,885 --> 00:44:39,415
Is there any point in continuing with this therapy?

567
00:44:41,755 --> 00:44:42,755
Tell me.

568
00:44:43,255 --> 00:44:45,955
Tell me what's really on your mind, Myo Jin.

569
00:44:47,855 --> 00:44:48,925
I'm scared.

570
00:44:50,995 --> 00:44:53,155
I'm in so much pain right now I feel like I could die.

571
00:44:55,235 --> 00:44:56,935
But what if there's more?

572
00:44:58,065 --> 00:45:01,505
- If there really is, I... - That's for you to decide, Myo Jin.

573
00:45:02,335 --> 00:45:04,045
It always has been.

574
00:45:05,105 --> 00:45:07,615
I've only been here to help, in my own small way.

575
00:45:10,015 --> 00:45:12,215
Human memory gets distorted.

576
00:45:12,985 --> 00:45:17,655
No one's memory stays perfectly intact.

577
00:45:18,485 --> 00:45:19,755
Distorted?

578
00:45:20,825 --> 00:45:23,095
Time changes everything.

579
00:45:23,895 --> 00:45:25,265
And memories are no exception.

580
00:45:27,235 --> 00:45:30,265
In the case of a major accident like the one you had,

581
00:45:30,935 --> 00:45:33,775
you have to be even more careful when assessing the situation.

582
00:45:35,435 --> 00:45:39,215
To steal your friend's boyfriend and then say you don't know why...

583
00:45:40,145 --> 00:45:41,985
That's a form of avoidance. Or it's an excuse.

584
00:45:43,115 --> 00:45:46,015
- Doctor, it really is not... - I know. It's neither of those.

585
00:45:46,485 --> 00:45:48,515
As your doctor, the Myo Jin I've come to know...

586
00:45:51,355 --> 00:45:54,295
genuinely doesn't know why she did what she did.

587
00:45:55,155 --> 00:45:57,324
- Then what is it? - I know this is hard,

588
00:45:57,325 --> 00:45:59,465
but try to be more patient.

589
00:46:00,335 --> 00:46:01,895
Because the truth...

590
00:46:02,565 --> 00:46:05,235
might be different from what you think it is.

591
00:46:06,435 --> 00:46:09,375
Could that really be true?

592
00:46:10,975 --> 00:46:12,055
We'll have to wait and see.

593
00:46:13,745 --> 00:46:17,915
You're already making great progress.

594
00:46:23,585 --> 00:46:26,295
(Jigu Electronics)

595
00:46:29,195 --> 00:46:30,725
No, that's a lie.

596
00:46:31,365 --> 00:46:36,065
On that day, this jerk brought us drinks and food himself.

597
00:46:42,105 --> 00:46:44,875
What's he talking about? That idiot.

598
00:46:45,005 --> 00:46:48,415
So he wouldn't leave a trail. He didn't take a card, only cash.

599
00:46:49,215 --> 00:46:52,715
He took another cut handing us over to those thugs, double-dipping.

600
00:46:53,015 --> 00:46:57,685
I've run this bar my whole life, and now I'm a human trafficker.

601
00:47:01,925 --> 00:47:02,925
Sir.

602
00:47:04,065 --> 00:47:06,565
Relax. No one's going to eat you alive.

603
00:47:07,265 --> 00:47:08,595
You can lose the scowl.

604
00:47:11,065 --> 00:47:12,465
It's messing up your handsome face.

605
00:47:12,875 --> 00:47:16,505
You'd think that we're the ones here to shake you down.

606
00:47:19,715 --> 00:47:21,175
All right, that's enough.

607
00:47:22,275 --> 00:47:24,885
If you're that bored, go get wasted somewhere else.

608
00:47:25,485 --> 00:47:28,085
What? Want me to recommend a place?

609
00:47:33,825 --> 00:47:35,255
You're a real character.

610
00:47:52,715 --> 00:47:53,715
What?

611
00:47:54,445 --> 00:47:55,815
What are you, their fixer?

612
00:47:56,545 --> 00:47:58,185
You came here to threaten me, is that it?

613
00:48:01,655 --> 00:48:02,655
All right, fine.

614
00:48:03,185 --> 00:48:05,105
I'm going to step into the kitchen for a minute.

615
00:48:05,425 --> 00:48:06,945
I have to prep for the dinner service.

616
00:48:08,055 --> 00:48:11,565
If you're still here when I'm back, pulling this nonsense,

617
00:48:14,135 --> 00:48:15,935
then I can't be responsible for what happens.

618
00:48:26,275 --> 00:48:29,515
- That idiot. - Take this "guest" outside.

619
00:48:32,485 --> 00:48:34,455
You're making a huge mistake. You hear me?

620
00:48:35,355 --> 00:48:37,885
For a business owner, you're so darn clueless.

621
00:48:39,225 --> 00:48:40,855
Why that little...

622
00:48:46,065 --> 00:48:47,135
Darn!

623
00:48:59,075 --> 00:49:01,675
Make another sound, and I'll snap your arm right off.

624
00:49:03,245 --> 00:49:06,455
Why is it you Korean scums never listen when I ask nicely?

625
00:49:09,185 --> 00:49:11,555
Do I need to repeat what I want to know?

626
00:49:11,985 --> 00:49:15,425
No, I'll talk. I'll tell you everything.

627
00:49:21,035 --> 00:49:22,095
This is just for show.

628
00:49:22,665 --> 00:49:23,665
Yes.

629
00:49:25,065 --> 00:49:27,735
Weird. You Korean guys...

630
00:49:28,175 --> 00:49:32,545
(Repentance)

631
00:49:38,645 --> 00:49:43,385
Open your eyes. Anyone with their eyes closed dies.

632
00:49:47,325 --> 00:49:48,325
Where are we?

633
00:49:52,695 --> 00:49:54,235
Today, I've got a special job for you.

634
00:49:54,735 --> 00:49:57,035
Teach this little punk a lesson.

635
00:49:57,605 --> 00:50:01,075
He's a scumbag who drugged our guy and stole his money.

636
00:50:01,505 --> 00:50:03,875
The boss gave the okay, so do whatever you want with him.

637
00:50:04,145 --> 00:50:05,245
Is he one of our guys?

638
00:50:05,505 --> 00:50:09,415
- No, he's a thug from Korea. - So we can do whatever we want?

639
00:50:09,845 --> 00:50:12,445
- Do whatever you want. I'm out. - No, wait.

640
00:50:13,385 --> 00:50:14,515
Wait, where are you going?

641
00:50:15,485 --> 00:50:16,625
Please, save me!

642
00:50:17,425 --> 00:50:19,285
Let go of me, you jerk!

643
00:50:24,265 --> 00:50:25,265
Sir!

644
00:50:28,795 --> 00:50:29,805
Sir!

645
00:50:30,505 --> 00:50:32,435
Pinky! This little punk...

646
00:50:32,905 --> 00:50:35,305
is that foreman's younger brother who gives you a hard time.

647
00:50:40,345 --> 00:50:42,445
Sir... Sir!

648
00:50:51,225 --> 00:50:52,585
Well, nice to meet you, you scum.

649
00:50:53,925 --> 00:50:57,765
Today, I'm going to beat all the fat right out of your gut.

650
00:51:07,735 --> 00:51:10,805
You sure took your sweet time. I seriously thought I was a goner.

651
00:51:11,805 --> 00:51:14,745
I had to pull every string I have just to track this down.

652
00:51:14,975 --> 00:51:18,415
Privacy laws are no joke these days. If you get caught, you're done for.

653
00:51:19,185 --> 00:51:20,815
Also, because of this whole thing,

654
00:51:21,015 --> 00:51:23,201
I should be billing for the business I lost at my shop...

655
00:51:23,225 --> 00:51:25,525
Are you absolutely sure it's Lee Jong Su?

656
00:51:25,785 --> 00:51:28,585
How many times do I have to say it? I've been doing this for 30 years.

657
00:51:28,755 --> 00:51:29,864
Trust me.

658
00:51:29,865 --> 00:51:32,825
Right. Take this before I forget.

659
00:51:33,065 --> 00:51:34,825
I fixed it, so it should work perfectly now.

660
00:51:35,365 --> 00:51:36,365
Thank you.

661
00:51:37,965 --> 00:51:41,135
So what's your main gig? The electronics shop or private eye?

662
00:51:41,475 --> 00:51:43,775
Dongdae Police Station, Violent Crimes Unit one.

663
00:51:44,175 --> 00:51:46,445
I was the top ace in the entire division.

664
00:51:46,975 --> 00:51:48,075
So what happened?

665
00:51:49,415 --> 00:51:51,055
Let's just say I messed up and got fired.

666
00:51:51,615 --> 00:51:54,055
How was I supposed to know where that money came from?

667
00:51:54,785 --> 00:51:56,401
After being unemployed for about two years,

668
00:51:56,425 --> 00:51:57,785
my wife took the kids and left me.

669
00:51:58,425 --> 00:52:01,395
But she won't grant me a divorce. It's driving me crazy. Darn it.

670
00:52:02,255 --> 00:52:03,795
So you got fired for taking a bribe?

671
00:52:04,365 --> 00:52:06,365
Hey! A bribe? Don't be ridiculous!

672
00:52:06,895 --> 00:52:08,295
You don't need to know the details.

673
00:52:10,065 --> 00:52:11,065
Hey!

674
00:52:13,075 --> 00:52:14,535
That's him. That's our guy.

675
00:52:17,845 --> 00:52:20,015
He's leaving right now.

676
00:52:20,315 --> 00:52:21,621
You've seen this in the movies, right?

677
00:52:21,645 --> 00:52:23,885
- We're about to do the best part. - The best part?

678
00:52:23,945 --> 00:52:25,815
The good guys go after the bad guy.

679
00:52:49,875 --> 00:52:51,845
But why is this car so slow?

680
00:52:52,305 --> 00:52:53,691
We're going to lose him at this rate.

681
00:52:53,715 --> 00:52:56,845
Lose him? We're only this close because I'm the one driving.

682
00:52:57,685 --> 00:53:00,985
Gosh, Lee Jong Su... That jerk.

683
00:53:01,955 --> 00:53:04,855
So what exactly are we supposed to find out from this guy?

684
00:53:05,325 --> 00:53:07,325
I can't do my job if I don't know what's going on.

685
00:53:08,355 --> 00:53:09,555
I can't tell you yet.

686
00:53:09,825 --> 00:53:12,095
You can't tell me? I'm the one you hired!

687
00:53:12,595 --> 00:53:14,295
You haven't forgotten who I am, have you?

688
00:53:14,765 --> 00:53:15,765
It's not that.

689
00:53:16,135 --> 00:53:19,875
- It's because I don't know either. - What? You don't know the reason?

690
00:53:20,205 --> 00:53:22,275
It looked like someone had something on Hee Soo.

691
00:53:23,105 --> 00:53:25,875
I asked her what it was, but she would never tell me.

692
00:53:26,175 --> 00:53:27,645
But Choi Hee Soo is dead.

693
00:53:28,945 --> 00:53:31,715
We must get the truth from him, the man who blackmailed her.

694
00:53:31,785 --> 00:53:34,615
You kidding? You think a guy like that will just talk?

695
00:53:35,355 --> 00:53:38,025
There's no other way. I have to find out, no matter what.

696
00:53:38,685 --> 00:53:39,885
Now that Choi Hee Soo is dead,

697
00:53:40,095 --> 00:53:41,724
- why find that out now? - The day Lee Jong Su...

698
00:53:41,725 --> 00:53:42,955
came to the studio,

699
00:53:43,465 --> 00:53:44,865
they both avoided me.

700
00:53:45,295 --> 00:53:48,465
Hey! Did I ask you for this pathetic amount of money?

701
00:53:48,665 --> 00:53:50,635
Who are you to be giving me money?

702
00:53:53,775 --> 00:53:56,305
- Hey! Who are you? - No! Myo Jin, don't!

703
00:53:57,005 --> 00:53:58,575
Don't. Just don't.

704
00:54:00,915 --> 00:54:03,815
- Hee Soo! - It's fine. I'll call you.

705
00:54:03,885 --> 00:54:04,885
Go.

706
00:54:10,585 --> 00:54:12,705
Choi Hee Soo and Lee Jong Su? Why would they do that?

707
00:54:12,825 --> 00:54:14,855
He has to know what the reason was.

708
00:54:15,695 --> 00:54:17,295
Considering they both avoided me,

709
00:54:18,265 --> 00:54:20,865
- I must be involved in this. - This had better be worth it.

710
00:54:28,335 --> 00:54:29,335
I'm getting out here.

711
00:54:50,895 --> 00:54:51,995
Did he go up?

712
00:54:54,595 --> 00:54:57,835
- He stopped on the second floor. - Okay, we need to hurry. Let's go!

713
00:55:05,245 --> 00:55:08,245
Quick, hide over here! We can't let him spot us!

714
00:55:09,445 --> 00:55:12,215
But what's the plan? We can't just follow him blindly.

715
00:55:14,055 --> 00:55:16,215
He's finishing up his conversation and heading inside.

716
00:55:18,655 --> 00:55:20,495
Judging by the photo of him at the entrance,

717
00:55:20,925 --> 00:55:21,925
I'd say he's the owner.

718
00:55:22,525 --> 00:55:26,295
What's this? A wine bar? You've got to be kidding me.

719
00:55:27,265 --> 00:55:28,265
Seriously,

720
00:55:29,235 --> 00:55:30,795
where did that jerk get all this money?

721
00:55:30,835 --> 00:55:32,735
So what are we supposed to do now?

722
00:55:35,675 --> 00:55:36,675
Here, take this.

723
00:55:37,305 --> 00:55:38,405
What is this?

724
00:55:38,945 --> 00:55:41,575
It's a cloning kit. All you have to do is plug this in,

725
00:55:41,745 --> 00:55:43,905
and a light on the kit will turn on and start copying.

726
00:55:44,145 --> 00:55:46,585
Even with a lot of data, a phone only takes one minute.

727
00:55:47,615 --> 00:55:49,515
Actually, no, wait. Is it two minutes?

728
00:55:49,855 --> 00:55:52,525
- Anyway, it's simple, right? - You want me to do it to his phone?

729
00:55:53,195 --> 00:55:54,395
By myself? Right now?

730
00:55:55,025 --> 00:55:58,065
If you want to know about someone, you look at their phone.

731
00:55:58,425 --> 00:56:00,435
Their entire life is in there.

732
00:56:00,695 --> 00:56:02,265
But what if I get caught?

733
00:56:02,865 --> 00:56:03,935
I can't do this.

734
00:56:05,105 --> 00:56:10,005
You think you can ask that jerk, "Why did you blackmail my friend?"

735
00:56:10,145 --> 00:56:13,575
You think he's just going to say, "Well, you see, the truth is?"

736
00:56:13,815 --> 00:56:17,785
This is the only way to find out what that jerk was plotting!

737
00:56:20,015 --> 00:56:21,915
What am I supposed to do?

738
00:56:22,155 --> 00:56:25,525
First, find that guy's office. Come on, hurry!

739
00:56:25,725 --> 00:56:28,055
- Go on! Hurry. - But...

740
00:56:33,865 --> 00:56:34,965
Welcome.

741
00:56:36,865 --> 00:56:37,865
This way, please.

742
00:56:44,945 --> 00:56:47,015
Excuse me. Where can I find the owner?

743
00:56:47,075 --> 00:56:49,985
He's with a client right now. Should I interrupt if it's urgent?

744
00:56:50,045 --> 00:56:52,515
No, it's okay. I can just wait until he's finished.

745
00:56:52,585 --> 00:56:54,585
All right. Let me know when you're ready to order.

746
00:57:14,935 --> 00:57:16,875
You're looking even better than last time.

747
00:57:16,945 --> 00:57:18,875
Really? I guess my money was well spent.

748
00:57:20,115 --> 00:57:22,575
I look forward to your favourable decision.

749
00:57:23,115 --> 00:57:24,515
Of course I'll invest.

750
00:57:25,115 --> 00:57:29,255
Thanks to you, this time should go smoothly too.

751
00:57:33,155 --> 00:57:36,665
Hey! Who's the owner here? Get out here, now!

752
00:57:36,925 --> 00:57:40,465
- Is it you? You? - Excuse me, sir. May I help you?

753
00:57:40,835 --> 00:57:41,835
I see.

754
00:57:42,365 --> 00:57:43,935
- So it's you. - Oh, my gosh!

755
00:57:44,005 --> 00:57:47,105
You're the jerk who made my wife divorce me!

756
00:57:47,375 --> 00:57:51,445
What lies did you tell her to make her serve me divorce papers?

757
00:57:51,505 --> 00:57:52,505
You scum!

758
00:57:52,575 --> 00:57:57,215
Sir, you can't be doing this here. Please, calm down first.

759
00:57:57,385 --> 00:57:59,485
Let's go over there and discuss this calmly.

760
00:57:59,615 --> 00:58:01,354
Calmly? You want me to be calm?

761
00:58:01,355 --> 00:58:03,055
Don't give me that "calmly" nonsense!

762
00:58:03,385 --> 00:58:06,625
You think I'm your customer? I'm your customer's husband!

763
00:58:06,695 --> 00:58:09,015
The husband of the customer you're messing with, you scum!

764
00:58:09,155 --> 00:58:11,365
- What? - What are you doing? Let go of him!

765
00:58:11,425 --> 00:58:13,871
You slept with my wife, didn't you? You think I wouldn't find out?

766
00:58:13,895 --> 00:58:17,035
See? You can't even deny it! You messed with the wrong guy!

767
00:58:18,605 --> 00:58:21,305
How many times? I asked, how many times?

768
00:58:21,475 --> 00:58:22,605
So you really did it?

769
00:58:25,745 --> 00:58:29,215
My wife's eyes were so bloodshot that I took her to the doctor,

770
00:58:29,445 --> 00:58:31,615
and they said she's a wine-aholic, you jerk!

771
00:58:31,785 --> 00:58:34,085
Look, just let go of me and we can talk!

772
00:58:34,685 --> 00:58:36,825
- What're you doing? Get him off me. - Yes, sir.

773
00:58:36,885 --> 00:58:37,925
What is wrong with you?

774
00:58:37,985 --> 00:58:40,855
Your plan was to ruin me, then take my wife and my money.

775
00:58:40,955 --> 00:58:43,271
Think you can get away with that? You've messed with the wrong guy!

776
00:58:43,295 --> 00:58:44,735
What are you talking about? Darn it.

777
00:58:44,965 --> 00:58:48,835
Hey, let go of me! I'll have all of you thrown in jail!

778
00:58:48,895 --> 00:58:49,895
Let go!

779
00:58:50,205 --> 00:58:51,205
Hurry.

780
00:58:55,635 --> 00:58:58,575
- Oh, no, what do I do? - Gosh, what a terrible day.

781
00:58:58,945 --> 00:59:01,175
Just my luck... Some crazy jerk has to show up.

782
00:59:02,545 --> 00:59:04,115
Hey! Where do you think you're going?

783
00:59:04,385 --> 00:59:06,855
Hey, you! You slept with my wife, didn't you?

784
00:59:06,955 --> 00:59:09,755
Did you think I wouldn't find out? Look at him! He can't even deny it!

785
00:59:10,385 --> 00:59:11,385
Hurry.

786
00:59:12,855 --> 00:59:15,325
How many times? I asked, how many times?

787
00:59:15,695 --> 00:59:17,825
So you really did it? Hey..

788
00:59:18,965 --> 00:59:20,165
You scum!

789
00:59:32,205 --> 00:59:33,205
Who are you?

790
00:59:33,975 --> 00:59:34,975
What?

791
00:59:36,345 --> 00:59:37,845
I...

792
00:59:40,615 --> 00:59:42,455
You've got a lot of nerve showing up here.

793
00:59:42,515 --> 00:59:46,355
Let me go! Let go of me! Let me...

794
00:59:47,095 --> 00:59:50,195
Sir! He's a cop!

795
00:59:51,395 --> 00:59:54,065
- What? - You're all dead! Assaulting a cop?

796
00:59:54,295 --> 00:59:56,195
- What? Darn! - What are you doing? Let go!

797
01:00:00,135 --> 01:00:01,135
Mister!

798
01:00:08,375 --> 01:00:10,345
Mister, are you all right?

799
01:00:12,345 --> 01:00:14,015
Wang Gi Cheol, that scum!

800
01:00:14,285 --> 01:00:15,715
We can't let that jerk get away!

801
01:00:16,555 --> 01:00:17,785
Right.

802
01:00:20,425 --> 01:00:21,425
Darn it!

803
01:00:25,725 --> 01:00:26,865
Hey, Lee Jong Su!

804
01:00:36,875 --> 01:00:38,705
Hey! Wait a minute!

805
01:00:45,815 --> 01:00:46,815
Darn!

806
01:00:52,455 --> 01:00:55,095
- Darn it! - I have a question for you!

807
01:00:55,755 --> 01:00:56,995
It'll only take a second!

808
01:00:57,465 --> 01:00:58,465
Darn!

809
01:01:06,735 --> 01:01:07,975
Call 911!

810
01:01:15,345 --> 01:01:16,345
Look...

811
01:01:18,545 --> 01:01:19,545
You vicious wench.

812
01:01:21,655 --> 01:01:22,735
Wasn't killing those two...

813
01:01:23,555 --> 01:01:24,825
enough?

814
01:01:27,095 --> 01:01:28,295
You can just stop now.

815
01:01:29,325 --> 01:01:30,465
This revenge of yours.

816
01:02:10,665 --> 01:02:15,505
(Reverse)

817
01:02:15,635 --> 01:02:18,105
Once we see what they exchanged, we'll have our answer.

818
01:02:18,305 --> 01:02:20,045
You killed my parents?

819
01:02:20,105 --> 01:02:22,745
I didn't think you'd find out this fast.

820
01:02:23,015 --> 01:02:25,045
So what should I do?

821
01:02:25,445 --> 01:02:28,815
- Stop him. - You did the Jebudo explosion?

822
01:02:28,885 --> 01:02:30,655
Yeah, well, that's all a bunch of bullshit.

823
01:02:30,985 --> 01:02:33,825
You don't need to know. It'll only put us both in danger.

824
01:02:34,225 --> 01:02:38,195
Thanks to you, I figured it out. What's been going on behind my back.

825
01:02:39,265 --> 01:02:41,071
That there's someone else targeting Ham Myo Jin...

826
01:02:41,095 --> 01:02:42,435
other than us?
